content:
✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: I like the idea of the challenge and how easy it can be solved.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Looks good to me. I like the last test case too.

The statement is good, but I got a bit confused when reading the last sentence,

"Based on a number of outlets, a number of dividers, and the number of sockets per divider, output the total number of powerSpots that you can arrange."

What is a divider? Is it the same as an extension cord?

I think this would make a great clash. It's a problem that can be simplified very easily, could even be solved in under 1 min if someone gets it quickly.

A few problems:

- LAN parties are now old fashioned :(

- I've never heard the word "dividers" being used in this context before. Normally people call them power bars or extension cords.

- "read divsockets string(40)" should probably be "loopline nDividers div_sockets:int"

- number of sockets should probably have a > 0 constraint, but that's a minor detail

Thanks a lot for your good comments!
- I changed LAN party to household appliances, but I'm a bit sad about it :-(
- One of the reasons I kept it in WIP was that I was uncertain about the terminology. Here (English not first language) we all call it dividers - but thanks for the suggestions! I shifted to extension cords (power bar sounds to me like something to eat. Cord sounds to me like only a cable - but when I google it I come to extension cords as well)
- Stub generator changed to loopline
- Constraints changed.

Whoops, thanks for spotting that one. Over here we all call it dividers, but ricemath already pointed me to the fact that this is actually not the correct naming, so based on his suggestion I shifted to extension cords. In that sentence I forgot to change it. From your reaction it is confirmed that it is an important change :-).

Thanks! I've corrected it.
Thanks. In real life the last case is not quite nice, but for this clash I intended it as a nice edge case, glad you like it :-).

Aww sorry didn't mean to make you change LAN party xD
I was just sad that LAN parties have become old fashioned, there's nothing wrong with the way you had it before. I see now that what I said could be easily misinterpreted, I apologize.

Np about the terminology, happy to help. Extension cord does sound like it's just a cable, I agree, but people use it to refer to power bars. And yes "power bar" does sound like a candy that would have a picture of Machamp on the wrap.
Ah I see - I'm going to change the LAN party back in, because it seems we totally agree. Indeed the fact that LAN parties are old-fashioned is a problem.
